A simple command line application that consumes a Public API using a HTTP client library.
This app will search wikipedia.com based on the string supplied as argument.

1. clone the application to your computer,
   Dependencies: 
   a. npm
   b. node
   c. xhr2
   run the commands below in terminal inside the application directory to install
      npm install -g
      npm install nodejs -g
      npm install xhr2 -g
      

The following commands will get 10 "hello world" articles from wikipedia 

    node libs/example.js hello world

    output will be an object of the following format
    { '1':
   { Title: ' Hello  World   program',
     Link: 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"Hello,_World!"_program' },
  '2': { Title: 'Hello', Link: 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hello' },
  '3':
   { Title: 'Hello World  disambiguation ',
     Link: 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hello_World_(disambiguation)' },
  '4':
   { Title: 'World Hello Day',
     Link: 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Hello_Day' },
  '5':
   { Title: 'Hello World   composition ',
     Link: 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hello_World!_(composition)' },
  '6':
   { Title: 'Hello Cruel World  Sole and the Skyrider Band album ',
     Link: 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hello_Cruel_World_(Sole_and_the_Skyrid
er_Band_album)' },
  '7':
   { Title: 'Hello Kitty',
     Link: 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hello_Kitty' },
  '8':
   { Title: 'Hello  disambiguation ',
     Link: 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hello_(disambiguation)' },
  '9':
   { Title: 'GNU Hello',
     Link: 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GNU_Hello' },
  '10':
   { Title: 'Hello World  Information Society album ',
     Link: 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hello_World_(Information_Society_album
)' } }

